# WebRTC PeerConnection conventions (macOS)

## Security baseline (DTLS/SRTP)
- ✅ **Always use DTLS/SRTP** for media + data. Reject any attempt to disable DTLS or SRTP (no “insecure mode” toggles).
- ✅ Treat DTLS/SRTP as a **hard requirement**, not an optimization: if the runtime cannot negotiate DTLS/SRTP, fail the connection setup with a clear error.
- ❌ Do not add configuration flags that silently downgrade security for “debugging”.

## PeerConnection setup checklist
- **MUST**: create `RTCPeerConnection` with explicit `RTCConfiguration` (don’t rely on implicit defaults).
- **MUST**: set `iceServers` explicitly (even if only STUN) and validate URL schemes (`stun:`, `turn:`, `turns:`).
- **PREFER**: create data channels with an explicit `RTCDataChannelConfiguration` and document reliability/ordering expectations.
- **DO NOT** expose every `RTCConfiguration` knob in public APIs. Expose a narrow, safe surface; keep advanced fields internal.

## Wrapper ↔ core boundary
- **Wrapper layer (ObjC/Swift API)**: validate user input, enforce security defaults, and produce user-facing errors.
- **Core layer (C++/lower-level WebRTC wiring)**: apply already-validated config; treat missing/unsafe config as programmer error.

## Examples

### ObjC wrapper (enforce secure defaults early)
```objc
RTCConfiguration *config = [[RTCConfiguration alloc] init];
config.iceServers = @[ [[RTCIceServer alloc] initWithURLStrings:@[@"stun:stun.l.google.com:19302"]] ];

// ✅ Create PeerConnection with explicit config
RTCPeerConnection *pc = [factory peerConnectionWithConfiguration:config
                                                     constraints:nil
                                                        delegate:self];

// ✅ Create DataChannel explicitly (no insecure toggles)
RTCDataChannelConfiguration *dcConfig = [[RTCDataChannelConfiguration alloc] init];
RTCDataChannel *dc = [pc dataChannelForLabel:@"file" configuration:dcConfig];
```

### C++ core (reject insecure policy if ever introduced)
```cpp
webrtc::PeerConnectionInterface::RTCConfiguration cfg;
// cfg.servers = ... (validated by wrapper)

// ✅ DTLS/SRTP required. If a product requirement ever adds a flag here,
// enforce: "secure only" and fail closed on mismatch.
// (Exact field names vary by WebRTC revision; keep the invariant.)
CHECK(IsDtlsSrtpEnabled(cfg)) << "DTLS/SRTP must be enabled";

auto pc = factory->CreatePeerConnectionOrError(cfg, constraints, observer);
if (!pc.ok()) { return pc.error(); }
```
